HEADWORD: Dress circle
<hw>Dress circle</hw>. <def>A gallery or balcony in a theater, generally
the first above the floor, in which originally dress clothes were
customarily worn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

